    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s lineup for April 10, 2026, is headlined by **Daulton Varsho** (72.16) and **Lawrence Butler** (72.16), who share the highest projected efficiency of the day. **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Woods Richardson, leveraging a 3% park boost and a strong 11% SP skill adjustment. Meanwhile, **Lawrence Butler** earns his spot at the top of the order with a 10% premium for batting leadoff, providing the necessary spark to ignite our offense. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (71.61) remains an elite utility play, maintaining high efficiency despite a slight platoon drag, while **Matt Chapman** (70.11) anchors the infield thanks to a massive 16% park boost against Baz, whose matchup also bolsters **Luis Arraez** (66.41) and **Jung Hoo Lee** (63.09). The inclusion of **Tyler Freeman** (69.05) is a calculated strategic move; while his raw base projection is modest, his potential for stolen bases against a slow delivery from Buehler makes him a high-leverage asset in our chase for speed.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Gavin Sheets** (57.91) on the bench. Despite a solid SP skill adjustment against Sugano, he fell just short of the 60.0 threshold required to displace our core, as the optimizer prioritized the speed-adjusted floor of our middle infielders. Similarly, **Gleyber Torres** (57.16) and **Yainer Diaz** (54.40) remain available as depth, though **Yainer Diaz** was penalized by a \"Lineup Pending\" status that necessitated a conservative valuation of his batting order. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Jeremiah Jackson** (59.51); while he offers intriguing upside, his placement in the 8-hole and the presence of an elite catcher behind the plate create a marginal floor. Outside of these concerns, the squad is well-positioned to capitalize on these specific park factors and platoon advantages, though we will continue to monitor weather patterns for any late-breaking changes that could impact the high-ceiling outlook for **Will Smith** and the rest of the crew.",
